%pyspark

def five_number_summary(v):
    v_sorted = np.sort(np.array(v))
    median = np.median(v_sorted)
    min, max = v_sorted[0], v_sorted[-1]
    
    first_half = v_sorted[v_sorted <= median]
    first_quartile = np.median(first_half)
    
    third_half = v_sorted[v_sorted >= median]
    third_quartile = np.median(third_half)
    return min, first_quartile, median, third_quartile, max

%pyspark

nums = [34, 25, 29, 38, 29, 30, 35, 37, 35, 28]
